Here are six of our coolest offshore robots




The future is autonomous, but robotisation in the oil industry is nothing new. Although the first automation appeared in the 80s and 90s, today we’re at the dawn of a new age of digitalisation. Here, we take a look at six of the coolest offshore robots working for Statoil.  






Meet our offshore robots
            






Solid financial results and strong cash flow in Q2



Good operational performance and high regularity gives us a good Q2 result. We expect a production growth of around 5 % in 2017.






Access all the numbers here
            










Latest news



Here are our latest news releases. For more news, see the link below.

















July 28, 2017

Byrding on stream

Statoil and its partners have started production on the Byrding field as planned. Recoverable volumes in Byrding are estimated at a good 11 million barrels of oil equivalent.


July 28, 2017











July 27, 2017

2017 second quarter and first half results

Statoil reports adjusted earnings of USD 3.0 billion and adjusted earnings after tax of USD 1.3 billion in the second quarter of 2017. IFRS net operating income was USD 3.2 billion and the IFRS net income was USD 1.4 billion.


July 27, 2017











July 27, 2017

Information relating to dividend and scrip dividend programme for second quarter 2017

Key information relating to the cash dividend to be paid by Statoil (OSE:STL, NYSE:STO) for second quarter 2017.


July 27, 2017










see all our news
            













Ready to be blown away?










This summer five wind turbines are sailing across the North Sea to their new home offshore Scotland. This will be the first floating wind farm in the world.






Learn more about Hywind
            













The key to competitiveness
A sit-down with Stéphane Garelli, Professor of World Competitiveness










“There is no secret to being competitive,” says Professor Stéphane Garelli, Professor Emeritus of World Competitiveness. “It takes resilience, agility and cost control—and one more thing…” We spoke to him after his presentation at Statoil Future Energy Forum in Stavanger. 






See the interview
            













Look what happens when chess champion meets Statoil employee
Financial analyst Erik Fossan played Magnus Carlsen










In his day job, Erik Fossan manages 90 billion NOK in our pension fund. In his spare time, he plays chess. But he’d never played world champion Magnus Carlsen—until one day in February.





See how it went
            










Current topics
















Hywind—the leading solution for floating offshore wind power

Hywind is the result of our knowledge from operating offshore for over 40 years combined with well-proven engineering from the world of renewables



Read more













Exploring the Barents Sea

As we open the door to the next chapter of the Norwegian oil adventure, we do so with a great sense of responsibility. Taking the quest for oil and gas further north is not a task we take lightly. 



Read more













Energy perspectives 2017

Energy Perspectives is an independent report prepared by Statoil’s analysts that presents a range of scenarios for energy consumption and climate change.



Read more

















Shaping the future of energy
We energise the lives of 170 million people.  Every single day.
















