“There is no secret to being competitive,” says Professor Stéphane Garelli, Professor Emeritus of World Competitiveness. “It takes resilience, agility and cost control—and one more thing…” We spoke to him after his presentation at Statoil Future Energy Forum in Stavanger. 






See the interview
            













Look what happens when chess champion meets Statoil employee
Financial analyst Erik Fossan played Magnus Carlsen










In his day job, Erik Fossan manages 90 billion NOK in our pension fund. In his spare time, he plays chess. But he’d never played world champion Magnus Carlsen—until one day in February.





See how it went
            










Current topics
















Hywind—the leading solution for floating offshore wind power

Hywind is the result of our knowledge from operating offshore for over 40 years combined with well-proven engineering from the world of renewables



Read more













Exploring the Barents Sea

As we open the door to the next chapter of the Norwegian oil adventure, we do so with a great sense of responsibility. Taking the quest for oil and gas further north is not a task we take lightly. 



Read more













Energy perspectives 2017

Energy Perspectives is an independent report prepared by Statoil’s analysts that presents a range of scenarios for energy consumption and climate change.



Read more

















Shaping the future of energy
We energise the lives of 170 million people.  Every single day.
















